    • Constructor Detail

      • TimeClusterFilterOption

        public TimeClusterFilterOption(java.util.List<Filter> filters,
                               java.time.LocalTime startTime,
                               long clusterTimeInMinutes,
                               long clusterSpacing)
        Filters given to the TimeClusterFilter will be applied to each timespan seperately.
        The timespans can be a fragmentation of the whole entry dataset, or, with a gap greater than 0, spans between the clusters will be excluded from filtering.

        For example, use TimeClusterFilter.DAY for clusterSpacing, to filter the same timespan of each day independently.

        Parameters:
        filters - list of filters, which will be applied to each timespan in a slicing process.
        startTime - start time of the timespan
        clusterTimeInMinutes - length of the timespan in minutes
        clusterSpacing - length of the gaps between each timespan in minutes
